results.query: Show me Apple's SEC filing timeline and patterns

baseline.response: Apple's SEC filings are available on the Apple Investor Relations website (investor.apple.com/sec-filings/default.aspx) and the SEC's EDGAR database (www.sec.gov/edgar/browse/?CIK=0000320193).  These include 10-K (annual reports), 10-Q (quarterly reports), 8-K (current reports), and other filings.  To identify patterns in the filing timeline, manual inspection of these filings is required to determine the frequency and timing of different filing types.  A visual timeline cannot be generated programmatically with the available tools.
